  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (Construction)",
  "description": "<p>· Taking off of quantities for building works</p>\n<p>· To prepare BQ, tender document, cost comparison for tender project including source and negotiate price with suppliers and sub-contractors, etc.</p>\n<p>· Project administration and documentation include preparation of sub-contract, VO, interim valuations and final account, etc.</p>\n<p>· To handle on-going project and resolve contractual issues with clients</p>\n<p>· To prepare shopdrawings, master programme, method statements and tender interview documents</p>\n<p>· To maintain proper tender and project documentation</p>\n<p>· To handle other assigned duties as required</p>\n<p>Requirement</p>\n<p>· Degree or Diploma in Quantity Surveying or Building/Construction/Civil Engineering</p>\n<p>· Able to work independently and under pressure</p>\n<p>· Proactive and well organized</p>\n<p>· Advanced AutoCad knowledge is required</p>\n<p>· MS Projects knowledge is advantageous</p>",
